I know I haven’t been super present on here lately; adjusting to life in a new city this year has been quite the journey. I don’t want to rant about all of the frustrations and disappointment it has come with. But I do want to say how thankful I am for everyone who has supported and encouraged us along the way. Every text, every DM, every “how ya doing” or word of encouragement really goes a long way. So from the bottom of my heart- thank you. Just wanted to take a minute to say that I love and appreciate all of you immensely 🫶🏻 @boohoomanofficial

My first tattoo in Portland finally happened!! I just so happen to work right down the street from an amazing shop here called @tattoosmilepdx. They’ve got a crazy roster of artists and if you haven’t already- you need to go give them a follow. But, working in the neighborhood over the past year I’ve gotten the privilege of getting to know @jasontylergrace, and yesterday I finally got my butt in his chair. We went into the session with a totally blank slate and came out with this sick freehand dragon. It felt great to get some new work done after a 1.5 year break. Huge salute to Jason for being a rad dude and for crushing this piece 🫡 Be sure to check out his page and go get a sweet tattoo from him! ⚡️ ⚡️ ⚡️

Hard to believe 2023 is almost over. It’s been a quiet year for me in this space; but a dramatically eventful one in real life. So much to process and navigate that I’ve hardly been able to find words to encapsulate the nature of the past year here with you all. This season of quietness and obscurity has been much needed, but has also been a frustrating and painful one. A time is coming when I will have language to express more of what I’ve been walking through; but for now, I just want to say that I hope you are all well and enjoying this holiday season. To everyone who’s still here- I love and appreciate you greatly. 🫶🏻🤝🏼 @boohoomanofficial

A few weeks ago we had a rare weekend with just my son, who at the time was about to turn 12 years old. We took him for hot chocolate and went to see the tallest tree in Portland @thesquarepdx, we shot photos (he took these btw) and just goofed around. That day/weekend was a precious reminder of why we are here in Portland and have chosen to climb the mountains we have over the past couple years. This holiday I am so thankful for the proximity we have because of those choices and the opportunities it has afforded us- despite what the journey has cost. Also, I couldn’t have done any of it without my rock @kasandra.mae; forever grateful that I get the privilege of doing life side by side with you. Merry Christmas, y’all 🫶🏻🎄🎁 ☕️
Just over here waiting on this snowstorm to show up… ⛄️ @boohoomanofficial
